Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with the development of a theory in homotopy type theory, which is a branch of mathematical logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper mentions the use of the Lean proof assistant to formalize most of the results. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the study of higher dimensional structures, which can be seen as a form of information. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper deals with the study of connective spectra, which can be seen as a geometric object. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the study of groups, which are important in game theory.
